                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/257: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-18T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. From the Ambassador. Your 593, November 16, 4 p.m. Please tell Aranha that
                    the Acting Secretary and I have both been pressing this matter continually at
                    the British Embassy here during the past fortnight. I am to speak on the subject
                    again with the British Chargé d’Affaires this afternoon. [Caffery.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
